    "body": "This PR adds a function `parsed_args_per_job_id`, which allows us to generate the exact configuration for any given buildkite job by using the `job_id`:\r\n\r\n```julia\r\nusing Revise; include(\"examples/hybrid/cli_options.jl\");\r\ndict = parsed_args_per_job_id();\r\nparsed_args = dict[\"sphere_aquaplanet_rhoe_equilmoist_allsky\"];\r\ninclude(\"examples/hybrid/driver.jl\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis should make analyzing performance easier since we can switch to specifying the job id instead of hard-coding all the exact specs, which can easily become out of sync with the buildkite jobs.",
